definitions.definition: Pointed in shape; having a point or points.
In the Raku programming language: being a block or subroutine that acts as a closure accepting a list of parameters (denoted by the pointed arrow symbol -> ).
examples: a pointy sub; a pointy block

main_definition: ( informal ) Pointed in shape; having a point or points.
